<p>After having completed the challenge, thanks to SSCx7832 <sup id="fnref:ssc" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:ssc" class="footnote" rel="footnote">11</a></sup> I discovered that also the second bypass technique was working and could be used as well to evade the regex checking for malicious PHP objects.</p>

